The paper discusses medium access control protocols and interference control in cognitive sensor networks, which are topics related to networked systems and communication in computer science. Therefore, cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also mentions cognitive radio, which is a technology that enables efficient spectrum utilization, and this falls under cs.IT (Information Theory). Additionally, the paper proposes interference-aware flooding schemes to optimize system performance, which is related to cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) and cs.SY (Systems and Control). Finally, the paper uses epidemic models and stochastic geometry to analyze the information delivery dynamics, which are topics related to cs.MA (Multiagent Systems).
